    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - OIL PAN INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OIL PAN INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Effective with Serial Number 593721 oil pans have been installed using a robotically-applied
                        liquid gasket. When replacing the oil pan use R.T.V. sealant as described below.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>On engines with S/N 593720 and Below.</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using guide studs, install the oil pan gasket and oil pan onto the crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the four cover spacers (if applied) and tighten the oil pan bolts and washers to
                    the specified special torque. Also, tighten the four longer bolts and washers at the rear of the oil
                    pan to the specified torque (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_160.xml" xrefid="ef4150787">7.87</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
